President Obama spoke with Belgian Prime Minister Charles Michel and French President Francois Hollande to congratulate them on the arrest of Salah Abdeslam, a suspect in the November 2015 ISIL terrorist attacks in Paris. The President commended the work of Belgian security services and highlighted the close cooperation between Belgian and French law enforcement authorities. He reiterated the United States' support in the fight against terrorism and reaffirmed their commitment to degrading and destroying ISIL.